#: ../../source/administration.rst:1285
msgid "Not allowed: patrons of this category will be *not* able to change their password through the OPAC regardless of the setting in :ref:`OpacPasswordChange`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1289
msgid "Minimum password length: enter the minimum password length for patrons of this category. Leave blank to use the default length set in the :ref:`minPasswordLength` system preference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1293
msgid "Require strong password: decide whether to enforce a strong password policy (at least one uppercase letter, one lowercase letter and one digit) for patrons of this category. By default, it will follow the rule set in the :ref:`RequireStrongPassword` system preference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1298
msgid "Follow the system preference :ref:`RequireStrongPassword`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1300
msgid "Yes: patrons of this category will be required to have a strong password regardless of the setting in :ref:`RequireStrongPassword`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1303
msgid "No: patrons of this category will *not* be required to have a strong password regardless of the setting in :ref:`RequireStrongPassword`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1306
msgid "Block expired patrons: decide if this patrons from this category are blocked from performing actions in the OPAC if their card is expired. By default it will follow the rule set in the :ref:`BlockExpiredPatronOpacActions` preference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1311
msgid "Follow the system preference :ref:`BlockExpiredPatronOpacActions`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1313
msgid "Block: patrons of this category whose membership has expired will be blocked from renewing and placing holds in the OPAC, regardless of the setting in :ref:`BlockExpiredPatronOpacActions`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1317
msgid "Don't block: patrons of this category whose membership has expired will *not* be blocked from renewing and placing holds in the OPAC, regardless of the setting in :ref:`BlockExpiredPatronOpacActions`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1321
msgid "Default privacy: choose the default privacy settings for patrons of this category."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1324
msgid "Default: checkout history will be kept indefinitely, until either the :ref:`batch\\_anonymize.pl script <cron-anonymize-patron-data-label>` is run or there is a manual :ref:`batch anonymization <patrons-anonymize-bulk-delete-label>` which is performed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1330
msgid "Never: checkout history is anonymized upon return. Statistics are kept, but the link between the checkout, the item and the patron is removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1333
msgid "Forever: checkout history is never anonymized for patrons of this category, regardless of the cron job or manual anonymization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1336
msgid "This setting can be edited by the patron via the OPAC if you allow it with the :ref:`OPACPrivacy` system preference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1339
msgid "Exclude from local holds priority: choose whether holds for patrons of this category are given a priority."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1342
msgid "Yes: holds for patrons of this category are not given special priority, regardless of the setting in :ref:`LocalHoldsPriority <localholdspriority-preferences-label>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1346
msgid "No: holds for patrons of this category are subjected to the setting in :ref:`LocalHoldsPriority <localholdspriority-preferences-label>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1349
msgid "Default messaging preferences for this patron category: assign advanced messaging preferences by default to the patron category"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1352
msgid "These default preferences can be changed on an individual basis for each patron. This setting is just a default to make it easier to set up messages when creating new patrons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1358
msgid "This requires that you have :ref:`EnhancedMessagingPreferences` system preference set to 'Allow'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1363
msgid "These defaults will only be applied to new patrons that are added to the system. They will not edit the preferences of the existing patrons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1366
msgid "If you need to apply the default preferences to existing patrons, you can force those changes by running the borrowers-force-messaging-defaults script found in the misc/maintenance folder. Ask your system administrator for assistance with this script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1374
msgid "Circulation and fines rules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1376
msgid "These rules define how your items are circulated, how and when fines are calculated and how holds are handled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1379
msgid "*Get there:* More > Administration > Patrons and circulation > Circulation and fines rules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1382
msgid "The rules are applied from most specific to less specific, using the first found in this order:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1385
msgid "same library, same patron category, same item type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1387
msgid "same library, same patron category, all item types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1389
msgid "same library, all patron categories, same item type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1391
msgid "same library, all patron categories, all item types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1393
msgid "default (all libraries), same patron category, same item type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1395
msgid "default (all libraries), same patron category, all item types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1397
msgid "default (all libraries), all patron categories, same item type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1399
msgid "default (all libraries), all patron categories, all item types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1401
msgid "The :ref:`CircControl` and :ref:`HomeOrHoldingBranch` also come in to play when figuring out which circulation rule to follow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1404
msgid "If :ref:`CircControl` is set to \"the library you are logged in at\" circulation rules will be selected based on the library you are logged in at"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1407
msgid "If :ref:`CircControl` is set to \"the library the patron is from\" circulation rules will be selected based on the patron's library"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1410
msgid "If :ref:`CircControl` is set to \"the library the item is from\" circulation rules will be selected based on the item's library where :ref:`HomeOrHoldingBranch` chooses if the item's home library  or its holding library is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1415
msgid "If :ref:`IndependentBranches` is set to 'Prevent' then the value of :ref:`HomeOrHoldingBranch` is used in figuring out if the item can be checked out. If the item's home library does not match the logged in library, the item cannot be checked out unless you are a :ref:`superlibrarian <patron-permissions-defined-label>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1423
msgid "At the very least you will need to set a default circulation rule. This rule should be set for all item types, all libraries and all patron categories. That will catch all instances that do not match a specific rule. When checking out if you do not have a rule for all libraries, all item types and all patron categories then you may see patrons getting blocked from placing holds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1433
msgid "Defining circulation rules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1435
msgid "Using the issuing rules matrix you can define rules that depend on patron category/item type combos. To set your rules, choose a library from the pull down (or 'Standard rules for all libraries' if you want to apply these rules to all branches):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1440
msgid "|image156|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1442
msgid "From the matrix you can choose any combination of patron categories and item types to apply the rules to"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1445
msgid "|image157|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1447
msgid "First choose which patron category you'd like the rule to be applied to. If you leave this to 'All' it will apply to all patron categories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1450
msgid "Choose the item type you would like this rule to apply to. If you leave this to 'All' it will apply to all item types for this patron category"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1453
msgid "If an item type has a parent item type, the rule will be displayed as Parent -> Child. The number of current checkouts will be limited to either the maximum for the parent (including sibling types) or the specific type's rule, whichever is less."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1458
msgid "|image1512|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1460
msgid "In the example above, there is a rule for the DVD item type with a maximum of 5 checkouts and a rule for Blu-ray, a child of DVD, with a maximum of 2 checkouts. A patron at this library will be able to check out a maximum of 2 Blu-rays in a total of 5 items of either DVD or Blu-ray types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1466
msgid "To summarize, a patron at this library would be able to take either : -  0 Blu-ray and a maximum of 5 DVDs -  1 Blu-ray and a maximum of 4 DVDs -  2 Blu-ray and a maximum of 3 DVDs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1471
msgid "Add notes about your circulation rule into the notes field. This can be helpful to remember why and when something was last changed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1474
msgid "Limit the number of items of this type a patron of this category can have checked out at the same time by entering a number in the 'Current checkouts allowed' field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1478
msgid "If you're allowing :ref:`on-site checkouts <onsitecheckouts-label>` then you may also want to set a limit on the number of items of this type patrons of this category can have on-site."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1484
msgid "This setting also depends on the :ref:`ConsiderOnSiteCheckoutsAsNormalCheckouts` preference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1488
msgid "Define the period of time an item of this type can be checked out to a patron of this category by entering the number of units (days or hours) in the 'Loan period' box."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1492
msgid "Define if the loan period should include closed days or not in the 'Days mode' column. The option chosen here will override the :ref:`useDaysMode` system preference for this particular rule."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1496
msgid "The 'Default' option will take the option defined in the :ref:`useDaysMode` system preference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1499
msgid "Choose the 'Calendar' option if you want to use the calendar to skip the days when the library is closed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1502
msgid "Choose the 'Datedue' option if you want to push the due date to the next open day"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1505
msgid "Choose the 'Days' option if you want to ignore the calendar and calculate the due date directly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1508
msgid "Choose the 'Dayweek' option if you want to use the calendar to push the due date to the next open matching weekday for weekly loan periods, or the next open day otherwise"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1512
msgid "Choose which unit of time, days or hours, that the loan period and fines will be calculated in in the 'Unit' column"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1515
msgid "You can also define a hard due date for a specific patron category and item type. The hard due date offers three options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1518
msgid "Exactly on: The due date of any item checked out with this rule will be set to the hard due date."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1521
msgid "Before: Koha will calculate the normal loan period. If the calculated due date would be after or on the hard due date, the hard due date will be used instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1525
msgid "After: Koha will calculate the normal loan period. If the calculated due date would be before the hard due date, the hard due date will be used instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1529
msgid "'Fine amount' should have the amount you would like to charge for overdue items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1534
msgid "Enter only numbers and decimal points (no currency symbols)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1536
msgid "Enter the 'Fine charging interval' in the unit you set (ex. charge fines every 1 day, or every 2 hours). The :ref:`finesCalendar` system preference controls wether the days the library is closed will be taken into account or not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1541
msgid "'When to charge' is most handy in libraries that have a fine charging interval of more than 1 day."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1544
msgid "End of interval: Given a grace period of 2 days and a fine interval of 7 days, the first fine will appear 7 days after the due date, it will always take one fine interval (7 days), before the first fine is charged."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1548
msgid "Start of interval: Given a grace period of 2 days and a fine interval of 7 days, the first fine will appear 2 days after the due date and the second fine 7 days after the due date."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1552
msgid "The 'Fine grace period' is the period of time an item can be overdue before you start charging fines. The :ref:`FinesIncludeGracePeriod` system preference controls if the grace period will be included when calculating the fine or not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1559 ../../source/administration.rst:1587
msgid "This can only be set for the 'Day' unit, not in 'Hours'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1561
msgid "The 'Overdue fines cap' is the maximum fine per item for this patron and item type combination."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1566
msgid "If this field is left blank then Koha will not put a limit on the fines this item will accrue. A maximum fine amount for all overdues can be set using the :ref:`MaxFine` system preference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1570
msgid "If you would like to prevent overcharging patrons for a lost items, you can check the box under 'Cap fine at replacement price.' This will prevent the patron's fines from going above the replacement price on the item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1577
msgid "If the 'Overdue fines cap' is also set, the fine will be the lesser of the two, if both apply to the given overdue checkout."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1581
msgid "If your library 'fines' patrons by suspending their account you can enter the number of days their fine should be suspended in the 'Suspension in days' field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1589
msgid "You can also define the maximum number of days a patron will be suspended in the 'Max suspension duration' setting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1592
msgid "The 'Suspension charging interval' option is just like the 'Fin charging interval'. For example, you could 'fine' a patron one day suspension for every two days overdue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1596
msgid "Next decide if the patron can renew this item type and if so, enter how many times they can renew it in the 'Renewals allowed' box."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1599
msgid "If you're allowing renewals you can control how long the renewal loan period will be (in the units you have chosen) in the 'Renewal period' box."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1603
msgid "If you're allowing renewals you can control how soon before the due date patrons can renew their materials with the 'No renewals before' box."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1607
msgid "Items can be renewed at any time if this value is left blank. Otherwise items can only be renewed if the item is due after the number in units (days/hours) entered in this box."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1611
msgid "To control this value on a more granular level please set the :ref:`NoRenewalBeforePrecision` preference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1614
msgid "You can enable automatic renewals for certain items/patrons if you'd like. This will renew automatically following your circulation rules unless there is a hold on the item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1620
msgid "You will need to enable the :ref:`automatic renewal cron job <cron-automatic-renewal-label>` for this to work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1626
msgid "This feature needs to have the \"no renewal before\" column filled in or it will auto renew every day after the due date."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1629
msgid "If you are using automatic renewals, you can use the 'No automatic renewals after' to limit the time a patron can have the item. For example: don't allow automatic renewals after a checkout period of 80 days."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1633
msgid "Similar to the hard due date setting, you can also stop automatic renewals after a specific date using the 'No automatic renewal after (hard limit)' setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1637
msgid "If patrons of this category can place holds on items of this type, enter the total numbers of items (of this type) that can be put on hold in the 'Holds allowed' field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1641
msgid "Leave empty to have unlimited holds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1643
msgid "If you'd rather put a hold limit per patron category, independent of the item type, see the :ref:`default checkout and hold policy by patron category <default-checkouts-and-hold-by-category-label>` section below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1648
msgid "If you want to have a hard hold limit, independent of patron category and item type, for this particular library, see the :ref:`Default checkout, hold, and return policy <default-checkouts-and-hold-policy-label>` section below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1653
msgid "If you want to have a hard hold limit, independent of patron category, item type, and across all libraries, see the :ref:`maxreserves` system preference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1657
msgid "You can also set a daily limit on the number of holds a patron can place."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1659
msgid "While the two settings before limit the holds that can be placed across various records, the next setting is used to limit the number of holds that can be placed on one record at the same time. For example, for fiction books you might want to allow only one item to be placed on hold at the same time by the same user. But for serials where items represent different issues more than one hold at the same time is fine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1666
msgid "Next you can decide how the availability of items influences the ability to place a hold. The 'On shelf holds allowed' option has three settings:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1669
msgid "Yes: This will allow to place holds on items at all times. It doesn't matter if they are available or checked out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1672
msgid "If any unavailable: This will allow to place a hold as soon as one or more items of the record are checked out. It doesn't matter if there are still one or more items available on the shelf."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1676
msgid "If all unavailable: This will allow to place a hold as soon as all items on the record are checked out that could fill the hold. This is especially useful for libraries that don't offer the service of getting items placed on hold off the shelf for patrons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1681
msgid "Under 'OPAC item level hold' you can decide if patrons are allowed to place item specific holds on the item type in question. The options are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1684
msgid "Allow: Will allow patrons the option to choose next available or a specific item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1687
msgid "Don't allow: Will only allow patrons to choose next available item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1689
msgid "Force: Will only allow patrons to choose a specific item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1691
msgid "If you want to allow patrons of this category to be able to place article requests on items of this type, choose an option in the 'Article requests' column"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1695
msgid "No: patrons of this category will not be able to place article requests on items of this type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1698
msgid "Yes: patrons of this category will be able to place article requests on items of this type, either on specific items (for example in the case of serial issues) or on entire records (for example in the case of monographs)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1703
msgid "Record only: patrons of this category will be able to place article requests on records of this type, but not on specific items"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1706
msgid "Item only: patrons of this category will be able to place article requests on items of this type, but not on entire records"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1711
msgid "If you want to use the article request functionality you need to enable it using the :ref:`ArticleRequests` system preference and configure the form using the other related preferences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1715
msgid "Finally, if you :ref:`charge a rental fee for the item type <adding-item-types-label>` and want to give this specific patron category a discount on that fee, enter the percentage discount (without the % symbol) in the 'Rental discount' field"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1720
msgid "When finished, click 'Save' to save your changes. To modify a rule, simply click the 'Edit' button either at the beginning or at the end of the row. The row of the rule being edited will be highlighted in yellow and the values will appear filled in at the bottom of the table. Edit the values at the bottom and click save."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration.rst:1726
